<paragraph id="02CC337233FE1E0E7132EDAE604DAE92" pageId="15" pageNumber="144">
<pageBreakToken id="CC8E97DD34101F5FC47211ACC091C9DF" pageId="15" pageNumber="144" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6325CC64219225258703522C7C22E40" pageId="15" pageNumber="144">
<bibRefCitation id="B3C0F1D2234FE3EB988F5A037AEFD10E" author="Hurd, Jr PD" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C." pageId="28" pageNumber="157" title="An Annotated Catalog of the Carpenter Bees (Genus Xylocopa Latreille) of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae)" year="1978">Hurd (1978</bibRefCitation>
: 23) listed this species from Brazil, Paraguay, possibly Colombia, and the provinces of Misiones and Salta in Argentina (Fig. 58). It occurs in the Paranaense biogeographic province (see comments below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FDD095277F60AACB97595AB96EE32CA" pageId="15" pageNumber="144" type="comments">
<paragraph id="679CE8488EA254448D8522981CE6702A" pageId="15" pageNumber="144">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2E4F715C94EDB3FB47695575728F5A0" pageId="15" pageNumber="144">
<taxonomicName id="D66D27E7B141599D12F569A8136C5A4D" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa pulchra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">Xylocopa pulchra</taxonomicName>
is known only from the female, and the male of 
<taxonomicName id="3BF5095F3862D2A9BBC67EFF7F6C6650" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa chrysopoda" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopoda">Xylocopa chrysopoda</taxonomicName>
may be conspecific with this species, as suggested by 
<bibRefCitation id="F5C0146F4B5A12FBA33A14FDD0800F4B" author="Schrottky, C" journalOrPublisher="Revista do Museu Paulista" pageId="30" pageNumber="159" pagination="330 - 613" title="Ensaio sobre as abelhas solitarias do Brasil." volume="5" year="1902">Schrottky (1902)</bibRefCitation>
. As for 
<taxonomicName id="01CC5F455D17B19DD0A639D4DDF7F685" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa bambusae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bambusae">Xylocopa bambusae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="826B3326E392FA7B2363D4F442A204B0" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa chrysopoda" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopoda">Xylocopa chrysopoda</taxonomicName>
, this species is rare in collections, and it has not been captured in the last 65 years. In addition to the type, we were only able to examine a historical specimen from Misiones deposited at MLP and specimen from Pocitos, Salta, deposited at USNM. The presence of this species in Colombia needs to be confirmed (
<bibRefCitation id="7270DC37036F62BB041C756868705DE0" author="Gonzalez, VH" journalOrPublisher="Acta Biologica Colombiana" pageId="28" pageNumber="157" pagination="31 - 40" title="Notas biologicas y taxonomicas sobre los abejorros del maracuya del genero Xylocopa (Hymenoptera: Apidae, Xylocopini) en Colombia." volume="14" year="2009">Gonzalez et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
